[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":1728},["ShallowReactive",2],{"content-query-6Lr5eWMrbT":3},{"_path":4,"_dir":5,"_draft":6,"_partial":6,"_locale":7,"title":8,"description":9,"date":10,"readtime":11,"tags":12,"body":19,"_type":1722,"_id":1723,"_source":1724,"_file":1725,"_stem":1726,"_extension":1727},"/blog/2024/games","2024",false,"","Curating my played videogames","A collection of the games I have played and reviewed with metadata fetched using the IGDB API","2024-10-10","6",{"language":13,"field":15,"type":17},[14],"python",[16],"gaming",[18],"script",{"type":20,"children":21,"toc":1707},"root",[22,31,46,51,56,61,67,115,128,171,206,249,284,297,321,327,332,369,381,554,560,573,594,620,633,669,688,700,733,738,743,853,865,871,883,978,984,989,994,1203,1216,1297,1311,1316,1352,1372,1378,1407,1412,1572,1599,1605,1617,1701],{"type":23,"tag":24,"props":25,"children":27},"element","h2",{"id":26},"preface",[28],{"type":29,"value":30},"text","Preface",{"type":23,"tag":32,"props":33,"children":34},"p",{},[35,37,44],{"type":29,"value":36},"In my ",{"type":23,"tag":38,"props":39,"children":41},"a",{"href":40},"movies",[42],{"type":29,"value":43},"previous post",{"type":29,"value":45},", I discussed consolidating my movie watchlist. In this article, I will explain how I am compiling a list of the video games I have played to date.",{"type":23,"tag":32,"props":47,"children":48},{},[49],{"type":29,"value":50},"I've always had a computer in my bedroom, ever since I can remember. In the early days of my childhood, I spent countless hours engaging with the imaginary hidden behind each and every pixel of my bulky CRT monitor. I catalogued a great many titles of old that are now relics of a time past, a time that I now look back at with tenderness and nostalgia.",{"type":23,"tag":32,"props":52,"children":53},{},[54],{"type":29,"value":55},"Safe to say that video gaming has been a hobby I've always enjoyed indulging in. The creativity and imaginary side of which, many people will be too quick to dismiss in favour of something deemed healthier for our bodies. Which is, in my opinion, partly true. It is indeed not a very active hobby, but health is not just of the body, but also of the mind. Video games have brought me joy on many different occasions: whether in displeasing moments of my life, as a pastime, or when the weather was not cooperative, or simply because I felt like it.",{"type":23,"tag":32,"props":57,"children":58},{},[59],{"type":29,"value":60},"Recently, I made some efforts to keep track of the movies I have seen. Now I want to do the same for video games. But, this time, I want to also give them a rating of my own and a small review. This short post will describe how I gather video game metadata (e.g. genre, platforms, etc.).",{"type":23,"tag":24,"props":62,"children":64},{"id":63},"gathering-video-game-metadata-from-igdb",[65],{"type":29,"value":66},"Gathering video game metadata from IGDB",{"type":23,"tag":32,"props":68,"children":69},{},[70,72,80,82,95,97,104,106,113],{"type":29,"value":71},"The Internet Game Database (",{"type":23,"tag":38,"props":73,"children":77},{"href":74,"rel":75},"https://www.igdb.com",[76],"nofollow",[78],{"type":29,"value":79},"IGDB",{"type":29,"value":81},") is an online database for video games initially launched in 2014 and owned by Amazon",{"type":23,"tag":83,"props":84,"children":85},"sup",{},[86],{"type":23,"tag":38,"props":87,"children":92},{"href":88,"ariaDescribedBy":89,"dataFootnoteRef":7,"id":91},"#user-content-fn-1",[90],"footnote-label","user-content-fnref-1",[93],{"type":29,"value":94},"1",{"type":29,"value":96},". Similarly to ",{"type":23,"tag":38,"props":98,"children":101},{"href":99,"rel":100},"https://www.omdbapi.com",[76],[102],{"type":29,"value":103},"OMDb",{"type":29,"value":105},", IGDB stores information about video games, including genre, game engine, company, and many others. IGDB also has a ",{"type":23,"tag":38,"props":107,"children":110},{"href":108,"rel":109},"https://api-docs.igdb.com",[76],[111],{"type":29,"value":112},"documented public API",{"type":29,"value":114}," that you can use to query against any video game in the database.",{"type":23,"tag":116,"props":117,"children":119},"h3",{"id":118},"trying-out-uv",[120,122],{"type":29,"value":121},"Trying out ",{"type":23,"tag":123,"props":124,"children":125},"strong",{},[126],{"type":29,"value":127},"uv",{"type":23,"tag":32,"props":129,"children":130},{},[131,133,139,141,146,148,154,156,162,164,169],{"type":29,"value":132},"I thought this small script was a good excuse to give ",{"type":23,"tag":134,"props":135,"children":137},"code",{"className":136},[],[138],{"type":29,"value":127},{"type":29,"value":140}," a try. ",{"type":23,"tag":134,"props":142,"children":144},{"className":143},[],[145],{"type":29,"value":127},{"type":29,"value":147}," is a new name in the realm of \"Python package and project managers\". What distances it from competitors like good-old ",{"type":23,"tag":134,"props":149,"children":151},{"className":150},[],[152],{"type":29,"value":153},"pip",{"type":29,"value":155},", or more modern, all-encompassing project managers, like ",{"type":23,"tag":134,"props":157,"children":159},{"className":158},[],[160],{"type":29,"value":161},"poetry",{"type":29,"value":163},", is that it is completely written in Rust under the hood. Claiming to be 10-100x faster than ",{"type":23,"tag":134,"props":165,"children":167},{"className":166},[],[168],{"type":29,"value":153},{"type":29,"value":170},", and boasting attractive features like inline dependency metadata, virtual environment management, managed Python versions, all the while also providing a pip-compatible interface, makes it a very strong contender for my new go-to Python package and project manager tool to be added to my toolset.",{"type":23,"tag":32,"props":172,"children":173},{},[174,176,181,183,188,190,196,198,204],{"type":29,"value":175},"To start any project in Python using ",{"type":23,"tag":134,"props":177,"children":179},{"className":178},[],[180],{"type":29,"value":127},{"type":29,"value":182},", similarly to what ",{"type":23,"tag":134,"props":184,"children":186},{"className":185},[],[187],{"type":29,"value":161},{"type":29,"value":189}," does, simply call ",{"type":23,"tag":134,"props":191,"children":193},{"className":192},[],[194],{"type":29,"value":195},"uv init ...",{"type":29,"value":197}," (use the ",{"type":23,"tag":134,"props":199,"children":201},{"className":200},[],[202],{"type":29,"value":203},"--help",{"type":29,"value":205}," flag if you feel lost). In my case, I ran the following command:",{"type":23,"tag":207,"props":208,"children":212},"pre",{"className":209,"code":210,"language":211,"meta":7,"style":7},"language-shell shiki shiki-themes dark-plus","uv init --name games --no-package\n","shell",[213],{"type":23,"tag":134,"props":214,"children":215},{"__ignoreMap":7},[216],{"type":23,"tag":217,"props":218,"children":221},"span",{"class":219,"line":220},"line",1,[222,227,233,239,244],{"type":23,"tag":217,"props":223,"children":225},{"style":224},"--shiki-default:#DCDCAA",[226],{"type":29,"value":127},{"type":23,"tag":217,"props":228,"children":230},{"style":229},"--shiki-default:#CE9178",[231],{"type":29,"value":232}," init",{"type":23,"tag":217,"props":234,"children":236},{"style":235},"--shiki-default:#569CD6",[237],{"type":29,"value":238}," --name",{"type":23,"tag":217,"props":240,"children":241},{"style":229},[242],{"type":29,"value":243}," games",{"type":23,"tag":217,"props":245,"children":246},{"style":235},[247],{"type":29,"value":248}," --no-package\n",{"type":23,"tag":32,"props":250,"children":251},{},[252,254,260,262,267,269,274,276,282],{"type":29,"value":253},"The ",{"type":23,"tag":134,"props":255,"children":257},{"className":256},[],[258],{"type":29,"value":259},"--no-package",{"type":29,"value":261}," flag tells ",{"type":23,"tag":134,"props":263,"children":265},{"className":264},[],[266],{"type":29,"value":127},{"type":29,"value":268}," that this project is not a Python package (in fact, it is just a small Python script). After running the abovementioned command, ",{"type":23,"tag":134,"props":270,"children":272},{"className":271},[],[273],{"type":29,"value":127},{"type":29,"value":275}," will generate the project directory structure for you, including the ",{"type":23,"tag":134,"props":277,"children":279},{"className":278},[],[280],{"type":29,"value":281},"pyproject.toml",{"type":29,"value":283}," file containing project metadata.",{"type":23,"tag":32,"props":285,"children":286},{},[287,289,295],{"type":29,"value":288},"Adding dependencies is as straightforward as it comes, e.g. to add ",{"type":23,"tag":134,"props":290,"children":292},{"className":291},[],[293],{"type":29,"value":294},"polars",{"type":29,"value":296}," as a dependency, simply call:",{"type":23,"tag":207,"props":298,"children":300},{"className":209,"code":299,"language":211,"meta":7,"style":7},"uv add polars\n",[301],{"type":23,"tag":134,"props":302,"children":303},{"__ignoreMap":7},[304],{"type":23,"tag":217,"props":305,"children":306},{"class":219,"line":220},[307,311,316],{"type":23,"tag":217,"props":308,"children":309},{"style":224},[310],{"type":29,"value":127},{"type":23,"tag":217,"props":312,"children":313},{"style":229},[314],{"type":29,"value":315}," add",{"type":23,"tag":217,"props":317,"children":318},{"style":229},[319],{"type":29,"value":320}," polars\n",{"type":23,"tag":116,"props":322,"children":324},{"id":323},"setting-the-dependencies",[325],{"type":29,"value":326},"Setting the dependencies",{"type":23,"tag":32,"props":328,"children":329},{},[330],{"type":29,"value":331},"For this small project, I selected the following dependencies:",{"type":23,"tag":333,"props":334,"children":335},"ul",{},[336,347,358],{"type":23,"tag":337,"props":338,"children":339},"li",{},[340,345],{"type":23,"tag":134,"props":341,"children":343},{"className":342},[],[344],{"type":29,"value":294},{"type":29,"value":346}," for data processing",{"type":23,"tag"